article.description: Elijah Olaniyi scored 19 points as Stony Brook edged past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 68-63 on Friday night. Makale Foreman added 17 points for the Seawolves, while Andrew Garcia chipped in 15.
article.headline: Olaniyi, Foreman lift Stony Brook past Texas A&M-CC 68-63
article.linkText: Olaniyi, Foreman lift Stony Brook past Texas A&M-CC 68-63
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Elijah Olaniyi scored 19 points as Stony Brook edged past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 68-63 on Friday night. Makale Foreman added 17 points for the Seawolves, while Andrew Garcia chipped in 15. Mouhamadou Gueye had eight rebounds and three blocks for Stony Brook (2-2). Myles Smith scored a career-high 22 points and had six rebounds for the Islanders (0-3). Jashawn Talton added 12 points. Nolan Bertain had seven rebounds. Stony Brook plays Texas Rio Grande Valley on Saturday. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi takes on North Dakota State at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
